  <li>In a large pan, heat 1 tbsp of oil with the onion and let it soften for 5 minutes.</li>
  <li>Add the coriander and chopped potatoes, let it cook for 1 minute.</li>
  <li>Add the peeled and chopped carrots with the vegetable stock. Cover it and let it simmer until the vegetables are soft, approximately 30 minutes.</li>
  <li>Once cooked, add the coriander and whizz the soup with a hand blender or in a food processor.</li>
  <li>Add salt and pepper</li>
  <li>Serve with coriander</li>
</ol>
